---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Use — Fractune">
  <nav class="nav">
    <div class="nav-inner">
      <a href="/" class="nav-logo">Fractune</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <main class="page">
    <div class="page-inner">
      <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="last-updated">Last updated: 17 April 2026</p>

      <h2>Acceptance</h2>
      <p>
        By using the Fractune app or visiting fractune.dk, you agree to these
        terms. If you do not agree, please refrain from using the service.
      </p>

      <h2>Purpose of the Service</h2>
      <p>
        Fractune is a tool for fractal fluence analysis of building facades.
        The app calculates a fractal dimension (D-value) based on the
        box-counting method and contributes results to a public dataset.
      </p>

      <h2>Contributions to the Dataset</h2>
      <p>
        When you analyse a building, you agree that the result will be published
        in the shared dataset. You do not retain copyright over individual
        analysis results, as they are factual measurements.
      </p>

      <h2>Acceptable Use</h2>
      <p>
        You may not use Fractune to submit false or manipulated data,
        overload the API, or attempt to identify other contributors.
        Misuse may result in your contributor ID being blocked.
      </p>

      <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        Fractune is provided "as is" without warranty of accuracy of analysis
        results. D-values are approximations and should not be used as the
        sole basis for professional or scientific decisions.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these terms. Significant changes will be announced in
        the app. Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance of the
        new terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions? Contact us at
        <a href="mailto:support@fractune.dk">support@fractune.dk</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .nav { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .nav-inner {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem;
    height: 52px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .nav-logo { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text); }
  .page { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .page-inner { max-width: 680px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 2rem; }
  h1 { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .last-updated { color: var(--color-text-secondary); font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  p { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
</style>
